  "remarks": "The Al-Aqsa Martyrs’ Brigade is a coalition of secular nationalist Palestinian militants that emerged during the Second Intifada in 2000. The entity’s principal aim is to establish a sovereign Palestinian state loyal to Fatah.; Listing: Instrument of first listing: Charter of United Nations (Anti-terrorism – Persons and Entities) List 2002 (No. 2) [F2021L00647, Gazette No. GN15, 17 April 2002].  Relisted on 6 November 2022, 13/09/2025 in Charter of the United Nations (Listed Persons and Entities) Amendment (No. 2) Instrument 2025",
